com.amazon.device.associates
Class SearchRequest

java.lang.Object
  com.amazon.device.associates.ShoppingServiceRequest
      com.amazon.device.associates.SearchRequest

public class SearchRequest
extends ShoppingServiceRequest

Represents a request to search for products in the Amazon product catalog using keywords or categories. This request is passed in ShoppingService.search(SearchRequest). Search results are returned in a paginated fashion. You can specify the page number to retrieve in the constructor of SearchRequest.

SearchRequest

public SearchRequest(java.lang.String category,
                     java.lang.String searchTerm,
                     int page)
Creates a new SearchRequest object to search for products based on category or search term. You can specify the search page to retrieve by specifying the page number. Page numbers must be non-negative integer. If you pass a page number that is graeter than the max page number, SearchResponse.Status will by INVALID_PARAMETER in SearchResponse. SearchResponse is returned as an argument to ShoppingListener.onSearchResponse.

Parameters:
category - The category of products to search.
searchTerm - The search term.
page - A specific page of results to retrieve. This must be a non-negative integer.
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if category or searchTerm is null or page is a negative integer.
